{"timestamp": "2025-12-05 11:30:00.015498", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Diagnostic report — SDN spine–leaf lab\nDate: (current run)\nScope: host-to-host reachability within 10.0.0.0/24 subnet across leaf_1 and leaf_2; status of OVS switches and management network.\n\nExecutive summary\n- Anomaly detected: Hosts in 10.0.0.0/24 cannot reach each other (100% ping loss). Pings fail immediately with \"Destination Host Unreachable\".\n- Localization: Problem localized to the OVS datapath / bridge instances on the switching nodes (leaf_1, leaf_2, spine_1). The physical host-facing NICs are UP, management interfaces (20.0.0.0/24) on switches are UP and carry traffic.\n- Root-cause hypothesis: The OVS bridge devices (switch datapaths) are in a DOWN state so L2 forwarding between host-facing ports is not functioning. As a result ARP/neighbor resolution fails and hosts cannot exchange L2 frames.\n\nObserved symptoms (high level)\n- All host-to-host pings show 100% loss with \"Destination Host Unreachable\" returned by the source host.\n- Host interfaces are configured (10.0.0.1–.4/24) but show zero RX bytes (no received traffic).\n- Switches' management interfaces (20.0.0.x) show rx/tx activity, indicating control/management plane interfaces are operational.\n\nKey evidence (selected outputs)\n- Ping failures (examples):\n  - host_1_1 -> host_1_2: 4 transmitted, 0 received, +4 errors, 100% packet loss; From 10.0.0.1 icmp_seq=X Destination Host Unreachable\n  - host_2_2 -> host_1_1: same pattern (Destination Host Unreachable, 100% loss)\n- Host interface status:\n  - host_1_1 eth0: inet 10.0.0.1/24, TX packets present but RX packets = 0\n  - host_1_2 eth0: inet 10.0.0.2/24, RX packets = 0\n  - host_2_1, host_2_2 same pattern\n- Leaf and spine switch interfaces and bridge states:\n  - leaf_1 shows:\n    - eth0, eth1, eth2: UP, LOWER_UP, master ovs-system (these are the physical ports)\n    - leaf_1 (OVS bridge device): flags=4098 … state DOWN\n    - ovs-system device: state DOWN\n    - eth3 (20.0.0.2 management): inet 20.0.0.2/24 and RX/TX counts present\n  - leaf_2: same pattern — host-facing eth0/eth1/eth2 are UP, but leaf_2 bridge device is state DOWN; eth3 management 20.0.0.3 UP with traffic\n  - spine_1: host-facing eth0/eth1 are UP (master ovs-system), but spine_1 bridge device state DOWN; eth2 (20.0.0.1) mgmt is UP with traffic\n- Interpretation of \"Destination Host Unreachable\": the source host's network stack cannot deliver frames to the destination on-link (ARP resolution failed or no L2 forwarding), so ICMP unreachable is generated locally.\n\nLocalization (which devices/components are at fault)\n- Primary components implicated:\n  - OVS bridges/datapaths on leaf_1, leaf_2, spine_1 (the logical bridge interfaces are DOWN).\n- Secondary (likely healthy):\n  - Host NICs and IP configuration (hosts have correct IPs and interfaces are UP).\n  - Management network between switches (20.0.0.0/24) appears functional — switches have 20.0.0.x addresses and RX/TX counts.\n\nRoot-cause analysis (most probable)\n- The OVS datapath/bridge instances are not active (bridge devices are DOWN). Although the physical ports (eth0/eth1 etc.) are up and enslaved to ovs-system, the logical bridge is not present/active, so frames from host ports are not being switched/forwarded at L2.\n- Consequence: ARP/neighbor discovery fails (no ARP replies), so hosts report \"Destination Host Unreachable\" for same-subnet targets. The fact that management interfaces show traffic indicates only the data-plane bridge(s) are affected, not the management plane.\n\nImpact\n- Full L2 connectivity among hosts in 10.0.0.0/24 is lost. Any services relying on host-to-host traffic across leaf switches are unreachable.\n- Control/management plane (20.0.0.0/24) appears intact, so controller connectivity and switch management may still be possible.\n\nAdditional diagnostic notes / recommended further checks (for investigation only — not remediation)\n- Confirm OVS daemons state on leaf_1/leaf_2/spine_1 (ovs-vswitchd/ovsdb-server) and check ovs-vsctl show to see whether bridges exist and which ports are attached.\n- Check OVS logs (ovs-vswitchd, ovsdb-server) for errors during bridge creation or datapath initialization.\n- Verify OpenFlow controller connectivity from switches (controller IP 20.0.0.100) and whether flows have been installed.\n- Inspect ARP table / neighbor entries on hosts to confirm ARP requests were sent and whether replies exist.\n- Capture packet traces on leaf host-facing interfaces to confirm whether frames reach the switch kernel and whether they are forwarded.\n\nConclusion\n- There is a clear anomaly preventing host-layer connectivity. The evidence strongly points to inactive OVS bridge/datapath instances on the switch nodes (leaf_1, leaf_2, spine_1) as the root cause. Management-plane connectivity remains available, limiting the problem to the data-plane switching function.\n\nIf you want, I can run the targeted checks next (ovs-vsctl show, systemctl status ovs* on the switches, OVS logs, or packet captures) to confirm the OVS daemon/bridge state and further narrow the root cause.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 10881, "output_tokens": 2689, "total_tokens": 13570, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 2688}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 1408}}}
